race.comment: CHILLCUZ (13) was unlucky not to score at Gawler, weaving through late and just missing. Rock-hard fit now and draws to settle closer. Ready. TESTING ONE TWO (4) shapes up beautifully fourth-up after a strong chasing effort at Murray Bridge. The sharp rise to the mile looks ideal and keeps Pannell. Genuine threat. DIRTY OLD TOWN (11) put them away with authority when storming home to shed her maiden. She'll drift back again from the draw, but if the tempo is genuine she'll be launching late. FLAMING EYES (5) can't be knocked, chasing a hat-trick and holding strong form. The draw is sticky, but the claim helps and she'll be charging home. SAINT BOOM (3) was no match for FLAMING EYES last time but maps to take much closer order from the inside alley. Don't dismiss.
